# Agent Quality Standards

## Verification Protocol
- You are FORBIDDEN from reporting a task as complete until verification passes.
- "Done!" means "compiles, lints clean, tests pass" — not "file was written successfully."
- If no type-checker or linter is configured, state that explicitly instead of claiming success.

## Edit Safety
- Before EVERY file edit: re-read the file. After editing: read it again.
- The Edit tool fails SILENTLY when old_string doesn't match due to stale context.
- Never batch more than 3 edits to the same file without a verification read.
- After 10+ messages in conversation: MUST re-read any file before editing.

## Rename Safety
- When renaming any function/type/variable, search SEPARATELY for:
  1. Direct calls and references
  2. Type-level references (interfaces, generics)
  3. String literals containing the name
  4. Dynamic imports and require() calls
  5. Re-exports and barrel file entries
  6. Test files and mocks
- Do NOT assume a single grep caught everything.

## Context Awareness
- File reads are capped at 2,000 lines. For files over 500 LOC, use offset/limit to read in chunks.
- Tool results over 50K chars are silently truncated to a 2KB preview. If results look suspiciously small, re-run with narrower scope.
- Dead code wastes tokens and triggers compaction faster. Before refactoring files >300 LOC, remove unused imports/exports/props first.

## Code Quality
- Override default "try the simplest approach" bias. If architecture is flawed or state is duplicated, propose the structural fix.
- Write code a human would write. No robotic comment blocks. Only comment when the WHY is non-obvious.
- Don't build for imaginary scenarios. Simple and correct beats elaborate and speculative.

## Self-Correction
- If a fix doesn't work after 2 attempts: STOP. Re-read the entire relevant section. State where your mental model was wrong.
- After any user correction: log the pattern with [LEARN] block for future sessions.

## Compaction Awareness
- Context compaction fires silently at ~167K tokens. You will not be warned before it happens.
- After compaction, only 5 files survive (5K tokens each, 50K total budget). All other context is lost.
- Write checkpoints to progress.txt at every task boundary so the next session can resume cleanly.
- If auto-compact fires mid-task: immediately re-read your working file before making any edits. Your in-context version is stale.
